   Beryl, the first hurricane of the the 2024 season. The National
   Hurricane Center provides forecasts of major storms, many of which make
   landfall in the United States. The Center is part of NOAA, the
   country's oceans- and atmosphere-focused agency. Experts say ongoing
   staff cuts at the agency could endanger some of its core missions, like
   forecasting weather.

